name: Bellsprout

Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Treecko
flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

name: Grovyle

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Sceptile

name: Sceptile

name: Seedot

Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a card, shuffle your deck, then put that card on top of it.

name: Torchic

name: Torchic
flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Blaziken-GX

name: Mudkip

name: Mudkip
flavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

name: Marshtomp

Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Swampert

Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.

name: Lotad

Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.

Attack1Text: This attack does 40 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Clamperl
flavorText: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Salamence
flavorText: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.

name: Latias â—‡
flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to each of your Basic Benched Dragon Pokemon.

name: Latios â—‡
flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokemon that dislikes fighting.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Evolution Dragon Pokemon in play.

name: Rayquaza-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your deck. If you do, attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of basic Grass and basic Lightning Energy attached to your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard your hand and draw 10 cards. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck. If you put any Pokemon onto your Bench in this way, you may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Wingull
flavorText: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they're circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokemon.

name: Pelipper
flavorText: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.
Attack1Text: Discard a Fire Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Slakoth
flavorText: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.
Attack2Text: Heal all damage from this Pokemon. It can't attack during your next turn.

name: Vigoroth
flavorText: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Slaking
flavorText: It is the world's most slothful Pokemon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, your opponent's Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Lazy.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. It can't attack during your next turn.

name: Whismur
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if you go second, and only on your first turn. Your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Whismur
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Loudred
flavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Exploud
flavorText: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremorâ€”or like an earthquake has struck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Skitty
flavorText: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Delcatty
flavorText: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may put 2 Supporter cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Kecleon
flavorText: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon has Unit Energy LightningPsychicMetal attached to it, it is a Lightning, Psychic, and Metal Pokemon.

name: Shiftry-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Electrode-GX
